{"key":"processedPost-8851304","value":{"id":8851304,"first":8851191,"last":8855769,"when":1220102347,"utime":"08/30/08 04:19 PM","cleanedPost":"As said, stacking vertical will keep the condensation to the top dish or two only.&nbsp; In addition, NEVER incubate petri dishes.&nbsp; Not only does that cause even more condensation, it promotes contamination.<br />After pouring the slightly warm agar(not hot), stack the dishes into a vertical stack and place the plastic sleeve back over them while they solidify.&nbsp; As soon as you inoculate always wrap with parafilm to provide filtered gas exchange.<br />Contamination is fairly normal on petri dishes.&nbsp; Anything on your print will germinate and grow on agar.&nbsp; You're supposed to make a series of transfers of your healthy mycelium to new dishes until you have a clean culture.<br />RR"}}